  "text": "The EAU guidelines on prostate cancer were first published in 2001 [CITATION_1] and since then have undergone several updates, up to the latest version in 2011 that can also be downloaded online [CITATION_2] . According to EAU guidelines, [CITATION_3] local staging (T-staging) should be based on findings from digital rectal examination (DRE) and in very specific cases from magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), even if the literature shows a wide range in the accuracy of T-staging by MRI, from 50-92% [CITATION_4] . The assessment of lymph-node status (N-staging) can be avoided in patients with stage T2 or less, PSA < 20 ng/mL and a Gleason score ≤6, as they have less than a 10% likelihood of having node metastases.",
